originalText.text: This is one of the best schools in the NY city public school systems. The staff is very helpful and concerned about their students. They work very close with the students and families for the each student's success and academic achievement. If your child is challenging and has gotten off track this school will definitely give them hope andnlead them back in the right direction.

originalText.text: Harlem Renaissance is one of the best High Schools in NYC. Each teacher and staff member played a significant role in my academic success. The environment allowed me to grow academically and socially. Not only are the teachers overqualified, they are resilient in motivating each student to excel. Ultimately , the schools goal is to assist students in embracing our unique  potential. Presently I'm a Psychology and Writing Major, with a minor in Criminal Justice. Without the help of Harlem Renaissance, I wouldn't have been able too attend Cedar Crest College, one of the most prestigious woman's colleges in Pennsylvania.
